					<div class="bio">
						<h4>Richard Bell</h4>
												<p>Richard Bell is a British-born, American-trained historian of the early United States. A professor of history at the University of Maryland, he has been an NEH Public Scholar and an Andrew Carnegie Fellow, among other honors. His previous book, <em>Stolen</em>, was a finalist for the George Washington Prize and the Harriet Tubman Prize.</p>
